text.tspan: of the underwriters.3.11REVIEW OF TECHNICAL CAPABILITYWhen reviewing and finalizing contracts Chartering department along with the Technical department shall analyse the technical capability of the vessel against theproposed work with the aim of identifying any incompatibilities and associated risks and verify that the proposed tasks are within the capability of nominated vessels.During the tenure of the contract the Technical and Operations Departments shall monitor the tasks that a vessel is being assigned by a client and ensure that vesselpersonnel have the required training and experience to perform all assignments safely.4RECRUITMENT AND MANAGEMENT OF SHIPBOARD PERSONNELThis section deals with the process of recruitment of shipboard personnel and their administration.The Fleet Personnel Manager has the responsibility for all aspects of manning and is supported by other staff in the Crew departmentin this purpose.4.1POLICY ON NATIONALITY OF CREWIt is the Company’s Policy to avoid large number of mixed nationalities on board our vessels to avoid any miscommunication and consequent breach of safety onboard.Cross-cultural values and attitudes are taken into consideration when placing staff on board.4.2EQUAL EMPLOYMENT WITHOUT ANY DISCRIMINATIONThe seafarer’s recruitment across the fleet shall be carried out without any discrimination based on· race or ethnic origin· colour or nationality· social origin· religious belief or activity· sex· marital status· sexuality and gender identity· physical features· political opinion, affiliation or activity· victimisation, once an initial complaint regarding one of the above attributes has been made.(However, any distinction, exclusion or preference in respect of a particular job based on the inherent requirements thereof shall notbe deemed to be discrimination)4.3RIGHT TO PRIVACY AND PROTECTION OF CONFIDENTIALITYThe confidentiality of seafarer’s personal data will be protected at all times.This data includes but is not limited to:a) his qualification;b) record of employment;c) personal data relevant to employment;d) medical data relevant to employment Such data will not be communicated to a third party unless prior approval is taken from the General Manager / Managing Director4.4EXPENSES INCURRED FOR RECRUITMENTIt is against the company’s policy to charge the seafarer for any of the below mentioned.Any recruitment fees for providing employment to the seafarerAny expenses or other charges which are borne directly or indirectly for providing employment to the seafarer(For the above purpose following shall not be deemed to be coming under the "recruitment fees or other charges for recruitment”1) Costs of the national statutory medical examination & certificates.2) Cost of obtaining the personal travel document and the national seafarer's book.)4.5RECRUITMENT AGE AND RETIREMENT AGE OF STAFFThe minimum age for seafarers joining a vessel shall be 18 years or higher.Age limits for new recruits are specified for each rank in the Qualification MatrixNormal retirement age of staff is 60 years.Exceptions can only be made with express approval of the General Manager in special cases and provided that candidate is dulycertified and medically fit.
